{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_BwWk4nx3B5cJcUPnv4rlHpkv","type":"tool_result","content":"   240→| Session desync между backend и frontend | Средняя/Средний | Polling с 30s interval; manual refresh fallback |\n   241→| Audit log storage growth | Высокая/Средний | Retention policy (90 дней); архивирование в cold storage |\n   242→| Polling endpoint overload | Средняя/Высокий | Rate limiting; caching; horizontal scaling |\n   243→| Breaking changes в существующей auth middleware | Низкая/Высокий | Feature flags; canary deployment; rollback plan |\n   244→\n   245→## 10. Открытые вопросы\n   246→Все критические вопросы закрыты. Ответы зафиксированы в AIDD:DECISIONS.\n   247→\n   248→- ~~Q1: Какие API требуют RBAC контроля~~ → Решено: все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n   249→- ~~Q2: Какая текущая реализация RBAC~~ → Решено: X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n   250→- ~~Q3: Какой frontend стек~~ → Решено: React + Zustand (not Redux)\n   251→- ~~Q4: Где хранить audit-логи~~ → Решено: БД (отдельная таблица)\n   252→- ~~Q5: Механизм синхронизации сессии~~ → Решено: Polling (30s interval)\n   253→\n   254→## 11. PRD Review\n   255→Status: NOT_READY\n   256→\n   257→### Summary\n   258→PRD contains critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings. The PRD assumes JWT-claims middleware and Redux, but research shows the system uses X-Profile-Key header auth and Zustand. These mismatches will cause implementation failures if not resolved.\n   259→\n   260→### Findings\n   261→- [ ] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"JWT-claims middleware\" (Q2=B) but research shows system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT. PRD section 2 and AIDD:DECISIONS incorrectly reference JWT.\n   262→- [ ] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A) but research shows frontend uses Zustand with persistence, not Redux.\n   263→- [ ] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **HIGH** — PRD requires WebSocket (Q5=A) but research shows SSE already exists and is used for flows/MCP. Need to evaluate SSE vs WebSocket decision.\n   264→- [ ] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **MEDIUM** — Research report shows Status: warn with open questions about Spring Security, JWT, and WebSocket that conflict with PRD decisions.\n   265→- [ ] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **MEDIUM** — PRD section AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS is empty, but research shows 3 unresolved questions (Q1-Q3 in research) about implementation approach.\n   266→- [ ] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **LOW** — Rollout plan section is a placeholder with no actual content.\n   267→- [ ] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **MEDIUM** — AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS lists paths like `src/middleware:src/auth` but research found no existing security configuration at these paths.\n   268→\n   269→### Action items\n   270→- [ ] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q2 from \"JWT-claims middleware\" to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" to match actual system architecture.\n   271→- [ ] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q3 from \"Redux\" to \"Zustand\" to match actual frontend state management.\n   272→- [ ] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — **Analyst/Architect** — Evaluate using existing SSE infrastructure vs implementing new WebSocket for role sync.\n   273→- [ ] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — **Researcher** — Close research open questions Q1-Q3 after PRD decisions are updated.\n   274→- [ ] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — **Analyst** — Add rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy to AIDD:ROLL_OUT section.\n   275→- [ ] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — **Analyst** — Synchronize all PRD sections (2, 6, 7, 8) with corrected Q1-Q5 answers.\n   276→\n   277→> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.\n   278→\n   279→## 12. История изменений\n   280→- 2026-03-18 — Initial PRD draft based on analyst answers (Q1=B, Q2=B, Q3=A, Q4=A, Q5=A) — Analyst Agent\n   281→- 2026-03-18 — Updated all sections (1-10) with synthesized requirements, filled AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS, set Status to READY — Analyst Agent\n   282→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e6496fc-389a-4569-9ddb-eb98a2998200","uuid":"461c02d2-01d9-4f51-9a23-b621f95a173e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md","content":"| Session desync между backend и frontend | Средняя/Средний | Polling с 30s interval; manual refresh fallback |\n| Audit log storage growth | Высокая/Средний | Retention policy (90 дней); архивирование в cold storage |\n| Polling endpoint overload | Средняя/Высокий | Rate limiting; caching; horizontal scaling |\n| Breaking changes в существующей auth middleware | Низкая/Высокий | Feature flags; canary deployment; rollback plan |\n\n## 10. Открытые вопросы\nВсе критические вопросы закрыты. Ответы зафиксированы в AIDD:DECISIONS.\n\n- ~~Q1: Какие API требуют RBAC контроля~~ → Решено: все мутационные API (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- ~~Q2: Какая текущая реализация RBAC~~ → Решено: X-Profile-Key header-based auth (custom middleware)\n- ~~Q3: Какой frontend стек~~ → Решено: React + Zustand (not Redux)\n- ~~Q4: Где хранить audit-логи~~ → Решено: БД (отдельная таблица)\n- ~~Q5: Механизм синхронизации сессии~~ → Решено: Polling (30s interval)\n\n## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: NOT_READY\n\n### Summary\nPRD contains critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings. The PRD assumes JWT-claims middleware and Redux, but research shows the system uses X-Profile-Key header auth and Zustand. These mismatches will cause implementation failures if not resolved.\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"JWT-claims middleware\" (Q2=B) but research shows system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT. PRD section 2 and AIDD:DECISIONS incorrectly reference JWT.\n- [ ] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A) but research shows frontend uses Zustand with persistence, not Redux.\n- [ ] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **HIGH** — PRD requires WebSocket (Q5=A) but research shows SSE already exists and is used for flows/MCP. Need to evaluate SSE vs WebSocket decision.\n- [ ] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **MEDIUM** — Research report shows Status: warn with open questions about Spring Security, JWT, and WebSocket that conflict with PRD decisions.\n- [ ] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **MEDIUM** — PRD section AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS is empty, but research shows 3 unresolved questions (Q1-Q3 in research) about implementation approach.\n- [ ] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **LOW** — Rollout plan section is a placeholder with no actual content.\n- [ ] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **MEDIUM** — AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS lists paths like `src/middleware:src/auth` but research found no existing security configuration at these paths.\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q2 from \"JWT-claims middleware\" to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" to match actual system architecture.\n- [ ] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q3 from \"Redux\" to \"Zustand\" to match actual frontend state management.\n- [ ] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — **Analyst/Architect** — Evaluate using existing SSE infrastructure vs implementing new WebSocket for role sync.\n- [ ] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — **Researcher** — Close research open questions Q1-Q3 after PRD decisions are updated.\n- [ ] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — **Analyst** — Add rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy to AIDD:ROLL_OUT section.\n- [ ] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — **Analyst** — Synchronize all PRD sections (2, 6, 7, 8) with corrected Q1-Q5 answers.\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.\n\n## 12. История изменений\n- 2026-03-18 — Initial PRD draft based on analyst answers (Q1=B, Q2=B, Q3=A, Q4=A, Q5=A) — Analyst Agent\n- 2026-03-18 — Updated all sections (1-10) with synthesized requirements, filled AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS, set Status to READY — Analyst Agent\n","numLines":43,"startLine":240,"totalLines":282}}}
