{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_9LDVqq1jjXAcUZjq9gfSiP5o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"tool_eKpLbKuCPlKgxoFIOqI14YHM","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md","old_string":"## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: NOT_READY\n\n### Summary\nPRD contains critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings. The PRD assumes JWT-claims middleware and Redux, but research shows the system uses X-Profile-Key header auth and Zustand. These mismatches will cause implementation failures if not resolved.\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"JWT-claims middleware\" (Q2=B) but research shows system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT. PRD section 2 and AIDD:DECISIONS incorrectly reference JWT.\n- [ ] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A) but research shows frontend uses Zustand with persistence, not Redux.\n- [ ] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **HIGH** — PRD requires WebSocket (Q5=A) but research shows SSE already exists and is used for flows/MCP. Need to evaluate SSE vs WebSocket decision.\n- [ ] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **MEDIUM** — Research report shows Status: warn with open questions about Spring Security, JWT, and WebSocket that conflict with PRD decisions.\n- [ ] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **MEDIUM** — PRD section AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS is empty, but research shows 3 unresolved questions (Q1-Q3 in research) about implementation approach.\n- [ ] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **LOW** — Rollout plan section is a placeholder with no actual content.\n- [ ] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **MEDIUM** — AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS lists paths like `src/middleware:src/auth` but research found no existing security configuration at these paths.\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q2 from \"JWT-claims middleware\" to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" to match actual system architecture.\n- [ ] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q3 from \"Redux\" to \"Zustand\" to match actual frontend state management.\n- [ ] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — **Analyst/Architect** — Evaluate using existing SSE infrastructure vs implementing new WebSocket for role sync.\n- [ ] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — **Researcher** — Close research open questions Q1-Q3 after PRD decisions are updated.\n- [ ] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — **Analyst** — Add rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy to AIDD:ROLL_OUT section.\n- [ ] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — **Analyst** — Synchronize all PRD sections (2, 6, 7, 8) with corrected Q1-Q5 answers.\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.","new_string":"## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: READY\n\n### Summary\nAll critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings have been resolved. PRD now correctly reflects: X-Profile-Key header-based auth, React + Zustand frontend, and polling-based session sync.\n\n### Findings — RESOLVED\n- [x] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q2 updated to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" (Q2=C). All PRD sections updated.\n- [x] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q3 updated to \"React + Zustand\" (Q3=B). All PRD sections updated.\n- [x] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **RESOLVED** — Q5 updated to \"Polling\" (Q5=B) as simpler approach aligned with system constraints.\n- [x] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **RESOLVED** — Research findings synchronized with PRD decisions.\n- [x] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **RESOLVED** — All open questions closed, documented in section 10.\n- [x] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **RESOLVED** — Rollout plan filled with 4 phases, feature flags, and rollback strategies.\n- [x] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **RESOLVED** — Research hints validated against actual codebase structure.\n\n### Action items — COMPLETED\n- [x] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — Changed Q2 from JWT-claims to X-Profile-Key header-based auth.\n- [x] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — Changed Q3 from Redux to Zustand.\n- [x] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — Changed Q5 from WebSocket to Polling (30s interval).\n- [x] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — Research findings synchronized.\n- [x] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — Rollout plan with phases and feature flags added to AIDD:ROLL_OUT.\n- [x] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — Sections 2, 6, 7, 8 synchronized with corrected answers.\n\n> Все пункты закрыты. Статус обновлён на `READY`."}}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":37272,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":37272,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e6496fc-389a-4569-9ddb-eb98a2998200","uuid":"60cd89e5-a8bf-4eff-9611-e26130ac586e"}
